{"title_page": "Union Investment", "text_new": "{{Primary sources|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Union Asset Management Holding AG\n| logo = Union Investment 2010 logo.svg\n| image          = Frankfurt.Maintor Porta.20150605.jpg \n| image_caption  = Union Investment headquarters in Frankfurt am Main.\n| trade_name = Union Investment\n| native_name = <!-- Company's name in home country language -->\n| native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-2 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. If there is more than one native name, in different languages, enter those names using {{tl|lang}}, instead. -->\n| romanized = \n| former type = \n| type = [[Aktiengesellschaft]]\n| traded_as = \n| industry = [[Investment management]]\n| fate = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| foundation = {{start date and age|1956|01|26|df=y}}\n| founder = \n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location_city = [[Frankfurt]]\n| location_country = [[Germany]]\n| locations = <!-- Number of locations, stores, offices, etc. -->\n| area_served = \n| key_people = {{ubl|Hans Joachim Reinke ([[CEO]]) | Alexander Lichtenberg | Alexander Schindler | Jens Wilhelm}}<ref>[https://unternehmen.union-investment.de/startseite-unternehmen/ueber-uns/unser-management.html \"Unser Management\"], Unser Management, Union Investment, retrieved 4 April 2020 {{in lang|de}}</ref>\n| products = \n| production = \n| services = \n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| aum = {{ubl|{{increase}} [[euro|EUR]] 368.2 billion <small>(2019)</small>}}<ref name=Kennzahlen/>\n| assets = \n| equity = \n| owner = \n| num_employees = 3,200<ref name=Kennzahlen/>\n| parent = [[DZ Bank]]\n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{URL|www.union-investment.de}}\n| footnotes = \n| intl = \n| bodystyle = \n}}\n[[File:View of the Union Investment-Skyscraper at a sunny winter day 2013.jpg|thumb|Union Investment former headquarters]]\n'''Union Investment''' (formal name '''Union Asset Management Holding AG''') is the [[Investment banking|investment]] arm of the [[DZ Bank|DZ Bank Group]] and part of the cooperative financial services network. It was founded in 1956 and is headquartered in [[Frankfurt]].\n\nTrading in [[open-end fund]]s occurs in part through the 1,101 [[credit union]]s in Germany (Volksbanken Raiffeisenbanken Co-operative, including Sparda-Banks, PSD-banks, etc.)<ref>[http://www.bvr.de/p.nsf/index.html?ReadForm&main=4&sub=20 \"Genossenschaftsbanken\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130626122300/http://www.bvr.de/p.nsf/index.html?ReadForm&main=4&sub=20 |date=June 26, 2013 }}, Bundesverband der deutschen Volksbanken und Raiffeisenbanken, retrieved 27 July 2013 {{in lang|de}}</ref> and in part through the external services of [[Bausparkasse Schw\u00e4bisch Hall]] AG, DZ Bank Group's [[building society]].\n\nThe primary shareholders in Union Investment are DZ Bank with 54.44% and [[WGZ Bank]] (the central bank of the credit unions in the [[Rhineland]] and [[Westphalia]]) with 17.72%.<ref>[http://unternehmen.union-investment.de/-snm-2130706433-1353410428-065f200000-0000000000-1353412158-enm-Unternehmen/UMH/Kennzahlen/Gesch_ftsbericht/GB_UMH_Korr_PDF.pdf Gesch\u00e4ftsbericht 2011], Union Investment (pdf), p. 161. {{in lang|de}}</ref> Other shareholders include [[BBBank]] and the credit unions through their membership associations.\n\n{{As of|2019|12|31|}}, Union Investment has self-declared [[assets under management]] of approximately 368.2 [[1,000,000,000|billion]] [[euro]].<ref name=\"Kennzahlen\">[https://unternehmen.union-investment.de/startseite-unternehmen/ueber-uns/unser-unternehmen/kennzahlen.html Kennzahlen], Kennzahlen im \u00dcberblick, Union Investment, retrieved 4 April 2020 {{in lang|de}}</ref>\n\n==Subsidiaries==\nUnion Asset Management Holding AG has 15 [[subsidiary|subsidiaries]],<ref>[http://unternehmen.union-investment.de/Unternehmen/UMH/Unternehmensprofil/T_chter_Beteiligungen/index.html \"Tochtergesellschaften und Beteiligungen\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318024949/http://unternehmen.union-investment.de/Unternehmen/UMH/Unternehmensprofil/T_chter_Beteiligungen/index.html |date=March 18, 2013 }}, Wer wir sind, Union Investment, retrieved 27 July 2013 {{in lang|de}}</ref> including:\n* Attrax S.A. in [[Luxembourg]] for [[investment fund|fund]]s [[brokerage]], distribution, share administration and custody services\n* Union Investment Institutional GmbH for [[institutional client]]s\n* Union Investment Institutional Property for institutional [[property investment]]s\n* Union Investment Luxembourg S.A. in Luxembourg\n* Union Investment Privatfonds GmbH offers open-end funds to private investors\n* Union Investment Real Estate GmbH (formerly DIFA Deutsche Immobilien Fonds AG) is the second largest German property investment association\n* Quoniam Asset Management GmbH follows a quantitative approach to investment and manages funds for institutional clients\n\n==History==\nThe Union-Investment-[[Gesellschaft mit beschr\u00e4nkter Haftung|Gesellschaft mbH]] was the third German investment association to be founded, on 26 January 1956, by 14 credit unions. The UniFonds [[stock fund]] was created the same year as its first open-end fund. The first offering of investment vehicles outside Germany was in 1961, in Belgium.\n\nCo op Immobilienfonds Verwaltung AG was founded in Hamburg in 1965 and in 1980 renamed Deutsche Immobilien Fonds AG or DIFA. The initial stockholders were the Central Institute of [[Consumer cooperative|Consumer Cooperatives]] and the [[Bank f\u00fcr Gemeinwirtschaft]]. In 1966 DIFA launched an open-end property fund, Co op Immobilienfonds, later renamed DIFA-Fonds Nr. 1 (DIFA Fund No. 1). Starting on 15 January 2007, DIFA did business under the name Union Investment Real Estate [[Aktiengesellschaft|AG]]; in 2009 it was converted to a GmbH.<ref>[http://realestate.union-investment.de/-snm-0184244822-1239199062-040ec00000-0000000066-1239260042-enm-docme/unternehmen/difa/wirueberuns/Chronik/index.html Chronik] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100513191220/http://realestate.union-investment.de/-snm-0184244822-1239199062-040ec00000-0000000066-1239260042-enm-docme/unternehmen/difa/wirueberuns/Chronik/index.html |date=May 13, 2010 }}, Union Investment Segment Immobilien, retrieved 27 July 2013 {{in lang|de}}</ref>\n\nSince 1967, Union Investment has offered management of investment accounts. In 1968, it offered its first retirement fund, UniRenta. In 1969, it reached a fund capitalisation of 1&nbsp;billion [[Deutsche Mark|DM]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://union-investment.biz/international/docme/unternehmen/ausland/com/profil/historie/index.html?nm_caller=crumbbar|title=Union Investment - Corporate history|website=union-investment.biz|access-date=2017-06-19}}</ref>\n\nUnion Investment Luxembourg [[S.A. (corporation)|S.A.]] was founded in 1988. The total capitalisation of the group was now 10&nbsp;billion DM.\n\nIn April 1994 Union Investment began offering stock-based wealth management with three strategic variants: chance, growth and security. In 1996 it introduced stock-based [[life insurance]] under the name OptiPlan.\n\nThe [[holding company]] Union-Fonds-Holding AG was founded in 1999 and changed its name in July 2002 to Union Asset Management Holding AG.\n\n==Distinctions==\nIn March 2013 Union Investment became the first investment association to be awarded five stars eleven times in a row in the [[investment fund]]s guide of the German business magazine ''[[Capital (German magazine)|Capital]]''.<ref>[http://www.fondscheck.de/news/Artikel-Union_Investment_Club_5_Sterne_Gesellschaften-4908371 \"Union Investment im Club der '5-Sterne-Gesellschaften'\"], Press release, Fondscheck.de, 12 March 2013, retrieved 27 July 2013 {{in lang|de}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.union-investment.de Union Investment website] {{in lang|de}}\n\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 1956]]\n[[Category:Investment companies of Germany]]\n[[Category:1956 establishments in West Germany]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Frankfurt]]\n", "text_old": "{{Primary sources|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Union Asset Management Holding AG\n| logo = Union Investment 2010 logo.svg\n| image          = Frankfurt.Maintor Porta.20150605.jpg \n| image_caption  = Union Investment headquarters in Frankfurt am Main.\n| trade_name = Union Investment\n| native_name = <!-- Company's name in home country language -->\n| native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-2 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. If there is more than one native name, in different languages, enter those names using {{tl|lang}}, instead. -->\n| romanized = \n| former type = \n| type = [[Aktiengesellschaft]]\n| traded_as = \n| industry = [[Investment management]]\n| fate = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| foundation = {{start date and age|1956|01|26|df=y}}\n| founder = \n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location_city = [[Frankfurt]]\n| location_country = [[Germany]]\n| locations = <!-- Number of locations, stores, offices, etc. -->\n| area_served = \n| key_people = {{ubl|Hans Joachim Reinke ([[CEO]]) | Alexander Lichtenberg | Alexander Schindler | Jens Wilhelm}}<ref>[https://unternehmen.union-investment.de/startseite-unternehmen/ueber-uns/unser-management.html \"Unser Management\"], Unser Management, Union Investment, retrieved 4 April 2020 {{in lang|de}}</ref>\n| products = \n| production = \n| services = \n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| aum = {{ubl|{{increase}} [[euro|EUR]] 368.2 billion <small>(2019)</small>}}<ref name=Kennzahlen/>\n| assets = \n| equity = \n| owner = \n| num_employees = 3,200<ref name=Kennzahlen/>\n| parent = [[DZ Bank]]\n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{URL|www.union-investment.de}}\n| footnotes = \n| intl = \n| bodystyle = \n}}\n[[File:View of the Union Investment-Skyscraper at a sunny winter day 2013.jpg|thumb|Union Investment former headquarters]]\n'''Union Investment''' (formal name '''Union Asset Management Holding AG''') is the [[Investment banking|investment]] arm of the [[DZ Bank|DZ Bank Group]] and part of the cooperative financial services network. It was founded in 1956 and is headquartered in [[Frankfurt]].\n\nTrading in [[open-end fund]]s occurs in part through the 1,101 [[credit union]]s in Germany (Volksbanken Raiffeisenbanken Co-operative, including Sparda-Banks, PSD-banks, etc.)<ref>[http://www.bvr.de/p.nsf/index.html?ReadForm&main=4&sub=20 \"Genossenschaftsbanken\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130626122300/http://www.bvr.de/p.nsf/index.html?ReadForm&main=4&sub=20 |date=June 26, 2013 }}, Bundesverband der deutschen Volksbanken und Raiffeisenbanken, retrieved 27 July 2013 {{in lang|de}}</ref> and in part through the external services of [[Bausparkasse Schw\u00e4bisch Hall]] AG, DZ Bank Group's [[building society]].\n\nThe primary shareholders in Union Investment are DZ Bank with 54.44% and [[WGZ Bank]] (the central bank of the credit unions in the [[Rhineland]] and [[Westphalia]]) with 17.72%.<ref>[http://unternehmen.union-investment.de/-snm-2130706433-1353410428-065f200000-0000000000-1353412158-enm-Unternehmen/UMH/Kennzahlen/Gesch_ftsbericht/GB_UMH_Korr_PDF.pdf Gesch\u00e4ftsbericht 2011], Union Investment (pdf), p. 161. {{in lang|de}}</ref> Other shareholders include [[BBBank]] and the credit unions through their membership associations.\n\n{{As of|2019|12|31|}}, Union Investment has self-declared [[assets under management]] of approximately 368.2 [[1,000,000,000|billion]] [[euro]].<ref name=\"Kennzahlen\">[https://unternehmen.union-investment.de/startseite-unternehmen/ueber-uns/unser-unternehmen/kennzahlen.html Kennzahlen], Kennzahlen im \u00dcberblick, Union Investment, retrieved 4 April 2020 {{in lang|de}}</ref>\n\n==Subsidiaries==\nUnion Asset Management Holding AG has 15 [[subsidiary|subsidiaries]],<ref>[http://unternehmen.union-investment.de/Unternehmen/UMH/Unternehmensprofil/T_chter_Beteiligungen/index.html \"Tochtergesellschaften und Beteiligungen\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318024949/http://unternehmen.union-investment.de/Unternehmen/UMH/Unternehmensprofil/T_chter_Beteiligungen/index.html |date=March 18, 2013 }}, Wer wir sind, Union Investment, retrieved 27 July 2013 {{in lang|de}}</ref> including:\n* Attrax S.A. in [[Luxembourg]] for [[investment fund|fund]]s [[brokerage]], distribution, share administration and custody services\n* Union Investment Institutional GmbH for [[institutional client]]s\n* Union Investment Institutional Property for institutional [[property investment]]s\n* Union Investment Luxembourg S.A. in Luxembourg\n* Union Investment Privatfonds GmbH offers open-end funds to private investors\n* Union Investment Real Estate GmbH (formerly DIFA Deutsche Immobilien Fonds AG) is the second largest German property investment association\n* Quoniam Asset Management GmbH follows a quantitative approach to investment and manages funds for institutional clients\n\n==History==\nThe Union-Investment-[[Gesellschaft mit beschr\u00e4nkter Haftung|Gesellschaft mbH]] was the third German investment association to be founded, on 26 January 1956, by 14 credit unions. The UniFonds [[stock fund]] was created the same year as its first open-end fund. The first offering of investment vehicles outside Germany was in 1961, in Belgium.\n\nCo op Immobilienfonds Verwaltung AG was founded in Hamburg in 1965 and in 1980 renamed Deutsche Immobilien Fonds AG or DIFA. The initial stockholders were the Central Institute of [[Consumer cooperative|Consumer Cooperatives]] and the [[Bank f\u00fcr Gemeinwirtschaft]]. In 1966 DIFA launched an open-end property fund, Co op Immobilienfonds, later renamed DIFA-Fonds Nr. 1 (DIFA Fund No. 1). Starting on 15 January 2007, DIFA did business under the name Union Investment Real Estate [[Aktiengesellschaft|AG]]; in 2009 it was converted to a GmbH.<ref>[http://realestate.union-investment.de/-snm-0184244822-1239199062-040ec00000-0000000066-1239260042-enm-docme/unternehmen/difa/wirueberuns/Chronik/index.html Chronik] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100513191220/http://realestate.union-investment.de/-snm-0184244822-1239199062-040ec00000-0000000066-1239260042-enm-docme/unternehmen/difa/wirueberuns/Chronik/index.html |date=May 13, 2010 }}, Union Investment Segment Immobilien, retrieved 27 July 2013 {{in lang|de}}</ref>\n\nSince 1967, Union Investment has offered management of investment accounts. In 1968, it offered its first retirement fund, UniRenta. In 1969, it reached a fund capitalisation of 1&nbsp;billion [[Deutsche Mark|DM]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://union-investment.biz/international/docme/unternehmen/ausland/com/profil/historie/index.html?nm_caller=crumbbar|title=Union Investment - Corporate history|website=union-investment.biz|access-date=2017-06-19}}</ref>\n\nUnion Investment Luxembourg [[S.A. (corporation)|S.A.]] was founded in 1988. The total capitalisation of the group was now 10&nbsp;billion DM.\n\nIn April 1994 Union Investment began offering stock-based wealth management with three strategic variants: chance, growth and security. In 1996 it introduced stock-based [[life insurance]] under the name OptiPlan.\n\nThe [[holding company]] Union-Fonds-Holding AG was founded in 1999 and changed its name in July 2002 to Union Asset Management Holding AG.\n\n==Distinctions==\nIn March 2013 Union Investment became the first investment association to be awarded five stars eleven times in a row in the investment funds guide of the German business magazine ''[[Capital (German magazine)|Capital]]''.<ref>[http://www.fondscheck.de/news/Artikel-Union_Investment_Club_5_Sterne_Gesellschaften-4908371 \"Union Investment im Club der '5-Sterne-Gesellschaften'\"], Press release, Fondscheck.de, 12 March 2013, retrieved 27 July 2013 {{in lang|de}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n