{"title_page": "Vettuvar", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n\n'''Vettuva gounder'''  refers to a social group of people in [[Tamil Nadu]], India, who once practised to do agriculture.\n\nThe name seems to have originated from ''Vettakar'' which means hunters. They are spread throughout Tamil Nadu. They are known as Vettuva gounder in the different regions of Tamil Nadu.{{cn|date=January 2019}}\n\nIn the southern Tamil Nadu districts of [[Tirunelveli district|Tirunelveli]] and [[Kanyakumari district|Kanyakumari]], they are known by the name Vettuvan (not to be confused with [[Vettuva]]) or Vetan. In the central Tamil Nadu districts of [[Thanjavur district|Thanjavur]], [[Nagapattinam district|Nagapattinam]], [[Tiruvarur district|Tiruvarur]] and [[Pudukottai district|Pudukottai]], they are known by the name Vettaikarar. In [[Coimbatore district]] and in [[Nilgiris district]] they are known by the name MalaiVedar. In [[Erode district]], they are referred Vettuva gounder.{{cn|date=January 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Social groups of Tamil Nadu]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n\n'''Vettuva gounder'''  refers to a social group of people in [[Tamil Nadu]], India, who once practised hunting but later adapted to agriculture.\n\nThe name seems to have originated from ''Vettakar'' which means hunters. They are spread throughout Tamil Nadu. They are known by the names Vettuvar, Veduvar, Vedar, Malaivedan,  Vettaikarar, in the different regions of Tamil Nadu.{{cn|date=January 2019}}\n\nIn the southern Tamil Nadu districts of [[Tirunelveli district|Tirunelveli]] and [[Kanyakumari district|Kanyakumari]], they are known by the name Vettuvan (not to be confused with [[Vettuva]]) or Vetan. In the central Tamil Nadu districts of [[Thanjavur district|Thanjavur]], [[Nagapattinam district|Nagapattinam]], [[Tiruvarur district|Tiruvarur]] and [[Pudukottai district|Pudukottai]], they are known by the name Vettaikarar. In [[Coimbatore district]] and in [[Nilgiris district]] they are known by the name MalaiVedar. In [[Erode district]], they are referred Vettuva gounder.{{cn|date=January 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Social groups of Tamil Nadu]]\n", "name_user": "2001:8f8:132b:c177:f4f7:23cd:a012:f008", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vettuvar"}
{"title_page": "Heosphora desertella", "text_new": "{{Speciesbox\n| image = \n| taxon = Heosphora desertella\n| authority = [[George Hampson|Hampson]], 1918\n| synonyms = *''Saluria desertella'' <small>Hampson, 1918</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Heosphora desertella''''' is a species of [[moth]] in the family [[Pyralidae]]. The species was first described by [[George Hampson]] in 1918.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/lepindex/detail/?taxonno=8212&page_no=1&page_size=30|title=LepIndex - desertella|website=www.nhm.ac.uk|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.biolib.cz/en/taxon/id1101611/|title=BioLib: Biological library|last=ondrej.zicha(at)gmail.com|first=Ondrej Zicha;|website=www.biolib.cz|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bie.ala.org.au/species/urn:lsid:biodiversity.org.au:afd.taxon:dfd17646-7fbb-428f-b52e-458f86cb9b13|title=Species: Heosphora desertella|last=Australia|first=Atlas of Living|website=bie.ala.org.au|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Pyralidae]]\n\n\n{{Pyralidae-stub}}\n[[Category:Moths of Australia]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1918]]\n", "text_old": "{{Speciesbox\n| image = \n| taxon = Heosphora desertella\n| authority = [[Hampson]], 1918\n}}\n\n'''''Heosphora desertella''''' is a species of [[moth]] in the family [[Pyralidae]]. The species was first described by Hampson in 1918.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/lepindex/detail/?taxonno=8212&page_no=1&page_size=30|title=LepIndex - desertella|website=www.nhm.ac.uk|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.biolib.cz/en/taxon/id1101611/|title=BioLib: Biological library|last=ondrej.zicha(at)gmail.com|first=Ondrej Zicha;|website=www.biolib.cz|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bie.ala.org.au/species/urn:lsid:biodiversity.org.au:afd.taxon:dfd17646-7fbb-428f-b52e-458f86cb9b13|title=Species: Heosphora desertella|las